headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 13 of his 21 points in the fourth quarter, and the Orlando Magic withstood a 44-point performance by the Hornets' LaMelo Ball to beat short-handed Charlotte 95-84 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Franz Wagner helps Magic overcome 44 points by LaMelo Ball to beat Hornets 95-84

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton finished with 34 points and 13 assists and made a season best nine 3-pointers on Monday night, leading the Indiana Pacers past the short-handed New Orleans Pelicans 114-100.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton scores 34 and delivers key plays in the clutch to send Pacers past Pelicans 114-110

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving had 32 points, six assists and seven rebounds, and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Atlanta Hawks 129-119 on Monday night without star Luka Doncic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kyrie Irving's big second half leads Mavericks past Hawks 129-119

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 20 points and the Boston Celtics made 22 3-pointers in a 126-94 win over the Los Angeles Clippers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kristaps Porzingis scores 16 in season debut, Celtics hit 22 3-pointers in 126-94 win over Clippers

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Memphis Grizzlies
New York Knicks at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — OG Anunoby scored a career-high 40 points, Jalen Brunson had 17 of New York's team record-tying 45 assists and the Knicks...
headlines.shortLinkText: Anunoby scores career-high 40 points, Knicks dish out 45 assists in a 145-118 blowout of Nuggets

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Dennis Schroder scored 31 points, Cam Thomas added 23 and the undermanned Brooklyn Nets rallied to beat Stephen Curry and the Golden State Warriors 128-120 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dennis Schroder leads short-handed Nets back from 18-point deficit to beat Warriors 128-120

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 37 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder’s bench players combined for 40 points in a 130-109 win over Sacramento on Monday night that extended the Kings' losing streak to four.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scores 37 and Thunder bench scores 40 in OKC's 130-109 rout of Kings
